# Handling uncertainty and hallucinations

- If you are not sure about any fact, API, file, or behavior, you must not invent details, names, paths, or URLs.

- When you lack sufficient information, you must explicitly say you do not know and mark it as [uncertain]. Example: I do not know which endpoint to call here [uncertain].

- When you are uncertain, first search the existing project files, tests, and docs to reduce uncertainty before responding.

- If, after investigation, uncertainty remains, ask me targeted clarification questions instead of guessing.

# Never fabricate:

- Non‑existent functions, classes, or modules.

- Fake API endpoints, parameters, or response shapes.

- Libraries or tools that are not already present in the project or clearly requested.